Create repo on github with readme and (node) .gitignore
- Clone the repo locally
- cd into project locally and `npm init`
- Populate index.js with skeleton app listener and '/' route on a get method
  -- NOTE - Do not forget to process.env.PORT
- npm install express --save
- Make sure package.json has a start script pointing to `start`: `node {your main server file such as index.js}`
- Log into heroku and create a new app
  -- Add heroku remote to local repo `heroku git:remote -a {app-name}`
- git add, commit and then `git push origin master`, `git push heroku master`
- If it works (:), `git checkout -b {branch_name}`
